Sentence: What a beautiful day!
what : exclamative determiner introducing the noun phrase
a : indefinite article, singular
beautiful : adjective, positive degree, modifying "day"
day : common noun, singular, head of the exclamative phrase
! : punctuation mark indicating exclamation

Sentence: How quickly he runs!
how : exclamative adverb modifying the adverb "quickly"
quickly : adverb of manner, modifying the verb "runs"
he : personal pronoun, third person singular, subject of "runs"
runs : verb, present simple, third person singular, intransitive
! : punctuation mark indicating exclamation

Sentence: What an incredible story!
what : exclamative determiner introducing the noun phrase
an : indefinite article, singular, used before a vowel sound
incredible : adjective, positive degree, modifying "story"
story : common noun, singular, head of the exclamative phrase
! : punctuation mark indicating exclamation

